The paper deals with age estimation from facial images, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The proposed model, Deep Regression Forests, involves joint learning of input-dependent data partitions and data abstractions, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and the non-stationary property of aging patterns, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR), respectively.
